# Viewer dev restart

After iterating on `web/` or export/viewer scripts, run:

```bash
make viewer-dev
```

This will:

1. `make build`
2. Stop any tuile server on `127.0.0.1:7710` (via `.tuile-dev.pid`)
3. Start `./bin/tuile serve --force` in the background
4. Run `scripts/viewer-demo-sessions.sh` (theme demo + plain shell)

Options via the script:

- `./scripts/viewer-dev-restart.sh --no-build` — restart + sessions only
- `./scripts/viewer-dev-restart.sh --no-sessions` — build + restart only

Server log: `.tuile-dev.log` in the repo root.

Use `SHELL=/usr/bin/zsh` (default in the script) so demo sessions spawn correctly.
